<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12021d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12021d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12021d"> 21(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tell in style of legend (Knock)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Alors que tant de l&eacute;gendes peuvent <font color="green">[8]</font> &ecirc;tre si ais&eacute;ment d&eacute;marqu&eacute;es qu&apos;il est possible, sans nuire &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t du r&eacute;cit, de changer les noms et les qualit&eacute;s des personnages ou de les transporter, sans inconv&eacute;nient, d&apos;un lieu dans un autre, celles du Mont-Saint-Michel ne sauraient &ecirc;tre modifi&eacute;es, ni dans leurs traits particuliers, ni m&ecirc;me dans leur physionomie g&eacute;n&eacute;rale; r&eacute;flexion faite, on se demande m&ecirc;me si ce sont bien l&agrave; des l&eacute;gendes. <br><font color="green">[While so many legends can so easily be demarcated that it is possible, without diminishing the story&apos;s interest, to change the names and the characteristics of the characters or to transport them, without difficulty, from one place to another, those about Mont-Saint-Michel cannot be modified, neither in their particularities, nor in their general form; when you think of it, they may not even be legends, after all.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 8-9</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Knock, a village in County Mayo where, in August 1879, two local women claimed to have seen apparitions on the church gable of Joseph, Mary and John. </mm> </dd></dl>
